<h1>Casual Use cases</h1>

<strong><u>Create a new commander 1.0</u></strong><br>
Create a new commander(casual version)<br>

<p>Player wants to create a new commander. The player names their commander the system will <br>
check if the name is valid. The player sets statistics for their commander, strength, intelligence and<br>
luck. The system checks if the total of these attributes add up to 30 (30 max)<br></p>


<strong><u>Use case 3.0: Create a new building</u></strong><br>
Create a new building(casual version)<br>

<p>The Player wants to create a new building, The Player will be presented with a list of buildings.<br>
The Player selects a building and the system checks to see if the player has the resources to build<br>
the selected building. If the player has the resources available they will be able to drag and drop<br>
their selected building to a chosen cell. The system checks if the target cell is free. If the cell<br>
is free then the selected building is constructed on the chosen cell. At any time prior to completing<br>
the building the Player can withdraw their building choice and resources will be reimbursed. The Use<br>
case ends when the building is complete.<br></p>


<strong><u>Use case 5.0:Create a new unit</u></strong><br>
<p>Create a new unit(casual version)<br>

<p>Player wants to delegate their army into units, The player will be shown a list of units. the player<br>
must selects a unit, The system will check if the player has the required building needed to house<br>
the unit.The player will select how many soldiers they want to delegate to that unit the system<br>
checks if the needed resources are there if they are the unit is created. The new unit will be<br>
created  The system  will reduce the army quantity after the unit is created.<br></p>





</body>
